____________________________________________________________________________________
Using the PluginGenerator (PluGen)

To compile, just type 'scons' from the PluMA root directory.

Note: This will produce a plugin in one of the following locations (in order):
1. ../plugins
2. PLUMA_PLUGIN_PATH; using directories in order.

USAGE
-----

./plugen [options] <pluginname> <command to run>

OPTIONS
-------

--lang=<language>   Specify the target language: cpp (default), rust
--help              Show help message

EXAMPLES
--------

Generate a C++ plugin (default):
  ./plugen MyPlugin mycommand -i inputfile -o outputfile

Generate a Rust plugin:
  ./plugen --lang=rust MyRustPlugin mycommand -i inputfile -o outputfile

PARAMETERS
----------

<pluginname>      Name of the new plugin
<command to run>  Command to run the software you want wrapped
                  Use 'inputfile' and 'outputfile' as placeholders

COMMAND SYNTAX
--------------

inputfile    - replaced with plugin input file path
outputfile   - replaced with plugin output file path
-flag param  - parameter read from input parameter file
[ ... ]      - optional parameters (enclosed in brackets)

GENERATED FILES
---------------

For C++ plugins:
  <pluginname>/
    <pluginname>Plugin.h    - Header file
    <pluginname>Plugin.cpp  - Source file with implementation
    README.md               - Documentation

For Rust plugins:
  <pluginname>/
    Cargo.toml              - Rust package manifest
    src/lib.rs              - Plugin implementation with FFI exports
    README.md               - Documentation

BUILDING RUST PLUGINS
---------------------

After generating a Rust plugin:

  cd plugins/<pluginname>
  cargo build --release

The compiled library will be at:
  target/release/lib<pluginname>Plugin.so

Copy it to your plugins directory to use with PluMA.
